step.action:
RUN THE PROLOGUE COMMAND — do NOT hand-drive its sub-steps. Invoke `tmux-cli e2e-bootstrap <scenario> [--project <path>] [--resume] [--orchestrator-pane %N]` (pass `--resume` per step 1b ONLY on an explicit resume directive; pass `--orchestrator-pane` with THIS conductor's own pane id if `$TMUX_CLI_ORCHESTRATOR_PANE` is not already exported). This single command performs, as hard gates, everything PROVISION/BOOTSTRAP/HANDSHAKE used to spell out by hand:
        • preconditions (tmux/docker/`docker compose`/claude on PATH);
        • REAP STALE TEST SESSIONS FROM PAST RUNS — enumerate via `tmux list-sessions` and `kill-session` only this conductor's disposable `tmux-cli-tmp-*` targets + orphan `/tmp/<scenario>-*` dirs from crashed prior runs, by EXACT name (NEVER `pkill -f`, which self-SIGTERMs the reap);
        • fresh-vs-`--resume` STATE_FILE clear/init/continue (step 1b / design §6);
        • resolve the target dir (`--project` or `/tmp/<scenario>-<UTCstamp>`), FAIL LOUD on a dirty dir, `git init`;
        • PRE-SEED `~/.claude.json` trust (`projects[<dir>].hasTrustDialogAccepted`+`hasCompletedProjectOnboarding`, top-level `bypassPermissionsModeAccepted`) BEFORE launch (config-then-run);
        • inject `TMUX_CLI_ORCHESTRATOR_PANE` into the tmux server env, then `tmux-cli start` the DETACHED target (auto-launches claude at the idle `❯` with trust pre-accepted + bypass on — the "N MCP servers need authentication" warning is irrelevant);
        • ATTACH THE HUMAN VIEW when a GUI exists — `$DISPLAY` set + a native terminal (konsole, gnome-terminal, xterm, alacritty, kitty, wezterm; Flatpak Konsole EXCLUDED as a no-host-TTY trap) → attach + VERIFY a client landed; headless ONLY with no GUI, announced as a WARN;
        • start the PIPE-PANE LOG (`-o` append) BEFORE any drive — the transcript of record;
        • send the INIT-PROMPT HANDSHAKE and PROVE `notify-orchestrator` is live (the target echoes `E2E-HANDSHAKE-OK <session>`, verified in the pipe-pane log).
